ğŸš€ Day 6 â€“ Embedded Software vs Firmware

In every embedded device, two important layers work together: Software & Firmware. Understanding the difference is key in automotive & EV systems.âš¡

ğŸ”¹ Firmware
Low-level code, stored in ROM/Flash.
Directly interacts with hardware.
Rarely changed, only updated when essential.
Example: Car ECU code, BIOS in PCs.

ğŸ”¹ Embedded Software
Runs on top of firmware/hardware.
Performs higher-level tasks & logic.
Can be updated frequently.
Example: EV battery management algorithms, Smart TV apps.

âœ¨ Key Difference:
Firmware = foundation (close to hardware).
Software = flexible (task-specific logic).

ğŸ’¡ Both together make devices intelligent â€” firmware ensures the system boots & talks to hardware, while software makes it â€œsmartâ€ for real-world applications.

